                            <comment id="13503205" author="erans" created="Fri, 23 Nov 2012 14:28:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a patch for this issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The additional test methods &quot;testMath905...&quot; explore the range where the previous code would overflow (around &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;709, 710&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;-710, -709&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please note that the tolerance for those tests had to be increased to &quot;3&quot; (whereas it was &quot;2&quot; for the range &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;-30, 30&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;OK to commit?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13503560" author="tn" created="Sun, 25 Nov 2012 21:32:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good to me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any specific reason why you prefer multiplication by 0.5 over division by 2, or just personal preference?&lt;br/&gt;
Searching in the FastMath source, there are several occurrences of both variants.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13503578" author="erans" created="Mon, 26 Nov 2012 00:03:05 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Any specific reason why you prefer multiplication by 0.5 over division by 2, or just personal preference?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve doing that since having read that multiplication is simpler (thus potentially faster) than division.&lt;br/&gt;
Never tried to benchmark.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
